# Backtesting (Required for MVP)

Every signal must be tracked from creation to resolution.

## What to Track

For each signal record in `signal_history`:
- Signal direction at time of creation
- Timestamp of creation
- Predicted move range (low%, high%)
- Time horizon (days)
- Actual price move when horizon expires
- Whether the prediction was correct (bool)

## Resolution Logic

When a signal's `horizon_days` has passed:
1. Fetch the actual price move from Yahoo Finance
2. Compare to predicted range
3. Set `was_correct = true` if actual move falls within range AND direction is correct
4. Store `actual_move` and `accuracy_notes`

## Performance Metrics to Track

| Metric              | Description                                      |
|---------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Accuracy            | % of signals where direction was correct         |
| Hit rate            | % of signals where move fell within predicted range |
| Confidence calibration | Do 70% confidence signals win ~70% of the time? |
| Avg move (by type)  | Average actual move for Bullish / Bearish signals |

## Minimum Target
- **≥50% prediction accuracy** for MVP launch

## Where to Show It
- Internal analytics page (not user-facing for MVP)
- Signal expanded view: "Historical Analog" section shows aggregate stats for similar past signals
